                                                                "title":  "Zombie Bear Notes",
                                                                "pages":  [
                                                                              "Zombie Bear Notes\n\nA Choascraft guide for zombie bear lore, danger, drops, and how their remains fit bear crafting.",
                                                                              "Lore\n\nSome redwood bears do not return to the soil. Infection holds the muscle, dulls the hunger, and leaves only the charge.",
                                                                              "Fact 1\n\nReal bears rely heavily on smell. A zombie bear keeps the shape of that hunter, but the instinct is bent by rot.",
                                                                              "Fact 2\n\nA sick or starving predator is more dangerous because its behavior becomes harder to read.",
                                                                              "Choascraft Zombie Bears\n\nZombie brown and zombie black bears use this loot table. They are hostile redwood threats.",
                                                                              "Combat\n\nTreat zombie bears like heavy melee enemies. They are not tameable and should not be handled like normal bears.",
                                                                              "Drops\n\nZombie bears drop Bear Rotten Meat and Bear Claw items.",
                                                                              "Rotten Meat\n\nBear Rotten Meat is the corrupted food drop. Keep it separate from Bear Raw Meat and Bear Cooked Meat.",
                                                                              "Bear Claws\n\nBear Claw items still matter. Use them in bear armor and claw recipes or as repair material for bear equipment.",
                                                                              "Gear Link\n\nNormal bear fur comes from brown and black bears. Zombie bears mainly provide rotten meat and claws.",
                                                                              "Redwood Warning\n\nWhen a bear does not breathe but still runs, the forest has already lost that fight."
